==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Asphodel
<hw>As"pho*del</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>asphodelus</ets>, Gr. <?/. See <er>Daffodil</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A general name for a plant of the genus
<gen>Asphodelus</gen>. The asphodels are hardy perennial plants, several
species of which are cultivated for the beauty of their
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is also popularly given to species of other
genera. The <xex>asphodel</xex> of the early English and French poets
was the daffodil. The <xex>asphodel</xex> of the Greek poets is supposed
to be the <spn>Narcissus poeticus</spn>.</note> <rj><au>Dr.
Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pansies, and violets, and <qex>asphodel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asphodelus</ent>⟦br⟧
